The poets. Now guess what, guys?

751
00:45:01,630 --> 00:45:04,510
In Greece, this was the complete opposite.

752
00:45:04,870 --> 00:45:06,710
They placed Homer

753
00:45:07,450 --> 00:45:09,450
at the very top of the society.

754
00:45:09,750 --> 00:45:14,250
Everyone wanted to be a
poet, like Homer, okay?

755
00:45:14,530 --> 00:45:17,150
So when Plato was writing the Republic,

756
00:45:17,490 --> 00:45:19,390
he was trying to become Homer.

757
00:45:19,550 --> 00:45:22,330
He was trying to become a
teacher of civilization,

758
00:45:24,230 --> 00:45:26,910
an inspirer of civilization,

759
00:45:27,390 --> 00:45:29,590
okay? A bigot of civilization.

760
00:45:30,070 --> 00:45:31,330
That's what Plato wanted.

761
00:45:31,510 --> 00:45:35,650
But guess what? Thucydides, when
he wrote the Peloponnesian War,

762
00:45:35,930 --> 00:45:37,170
he was trying to do the same thing.

763
00:45:37,350 --> 00:45:39,810
He was trying to inspire civilization.

764
00:45:40,370 --> 00:45:42,450
He was trying to inspire new ideas.

765
00:45:43,390 --> 00:45:44,950
Because they all wanted to become Homer.

766
00:45:45,550 --> 00:45:49,350
Okay? Because they all knew Homer
was the father of civilization.

767
00:45:49,870 --> 00:45:51,490
And they wanted to continue his legacy.

768
00:45:52,790 --> 00:45:55,910
And that's what made the Greeks
unique in human history.

769
00:45:56,230 --> 00:45:59,810
Because only the society put poets first

770
00:45:59,810 --> 00:46:01,250
and foremost at the top.

771
00:46:01,470 --> 00:46:03,210
And no other society did so, okay?

772
00:46:03,390 --> 00:46:04,650
In China, it was the complete opposite.

773
00:46:04,970 --> 00:46:06,290
Because if you're a scholar official,

774
00:46:06,670 --> 00:46:10,310
what you're most afraid of is
independent thinking, okay?

775
00:46:10,670 --> 00:46:11,910
So censorship. Censorship.

776
00:46:15,210 --> 00:46:17,330
Censorship was their main role, okay?

777
00:46:18,210 --> 00:46:20,550
Controlling how people
thought through censorship.

778
00:46:20,990 --> 00:46:26,790
And that's why China never really
produced a Homer or a great thinker.

779
00:46:27,730 --> 00:46:29,750
Okay? Does that make sense? All right?

780
00:46:30,530 --> 00:46:33,310
And so, this is going to be strange,

781
00:46:33,610 --> 00:46:35,050
but it's only because

782
00:46:35,050 --> 00:46:39,230
Greece got destroyed at
the end of the Bronze Age.

783
00:46:40,490 --> 00:46:42,410
It became decentralized. It lived in poor.

